    <h2 id="science-of-sour">The Science of Sour: How Vegan Gummies Deliver the Pucker</h2>

    <p>Sour taste perception begins with hydrogen ions (H+) activating the PKD2L1 ion channel in Type III taste receptor cells on your tongue. The higher the concentration of free hydrogen ions — meaning the lower the pH — the more intense the sour sensation. Every food-grade acid used in sour candy works by this same mechanism, but they differ dramatically in their sour "profile": how quickly the sourness hits, how long it lingers, and what secondary flavors accompany it.</p>

    <div class="key-stat">
